<servinfosub id = "AENAP70BA804003002">
<title>
Diagnosis Procedure
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to perform 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804001">CAN Communication Check</intxref>
 before following this procedure.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Occurrence of multiple troubles is not included in the scope of this trouble diagnosis.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
When “Lost Communication” is detected in any control module, perform diagnosing according to the following procedure.
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect SUZUKI scan tool to DLC.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select “Communication Bus Check” under “Bus Check” menu of SUZUKI scan tool and check for disabled communicating control module (it is not displayed on screen).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Based on above check results, select applicable diagnosis flow ([a] to [k]) from 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804003003">Diagnosis Flow Selection Table</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Perform troubleshooting according to selected diagnosis flow.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<p-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70BA804003003">
<title>
Diagnosis Flow Selection Table
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
If an individual control module or sensor fails to communicate, check whether power supply circuit or ground circuit of control module or sensor is in good condition, by referring to system circuit diagram, etc. before diagnosing trouble with flow chart.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If it is not possible to select suitable diagnosis flow from “Diagnosis Flow Selection Table” or “two or more diagnosis flows are selectable”, perform 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804004">Troubleshooting for Communication Bus Off</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Diagnosis flows [a] to [k] link with CAN communication lines [a] to [k] of 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70BA804003001">Circuit Diagram</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
